TITLE: Implementing Custom Authorizer Function with Casbin
DESCRIPTION: Example of using a custom authorizer function with Casbin middleware. This allows for complete customization of the authorization logic, extracting user, path, and method information from the context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/honojs/middleware/blob/main/packages/casbin/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { Hono } from 'hono'
import { newEnforcer } from 'casbin'
import { casbin } from '@hono/casbin'

const app = new Hono()
app.use(
  '*',
  casbin({
    newEnforcer: newEnforcer('path-to-your-model.conf', 'path-to-your-policy.csv'),
    authorizer: async (c, enforcer) => {
      const { user, path, method } = c
      return await enforcer.enforce(user, path, method)
    },
  })
)
```

