TITLE: Validating Form Data with Zod in Hono Middleware
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the Conform validator middleware with Zod schema in a Hono application. It validates the 'name' and 'age' fields of the submitted form data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/honojs/middleware/blob/main/packages/conform-validator/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { z } from 'zod'
import { parseWithZod } from '@conform-to/zod'
import { conformValidator } from '@hono/conform-validator'
import { HTTPException } from 'hono/http-exception'

const schema = z.object({
  name: z.string(),
  age: z.string(),
})

app.post(
  '/author',
  conformValidator((formData) => parseWithZod(formData, { schema })),
  (c) => {
    const submission = c.req.valid('form')
    const data = submission.value

    return c.json({ success: true, message: `${data.name} is ${data.age}` })
  }
)
```

